caption:
Mike Tyson and Floyd Mayweather have agreed to face each other in a blockbuster exhibition fight in 2026 🤯🥊

🗣️ Tyson: “This fight is something neither the world nor I ever thought would or could happen. I still can’t believe Floyd wants to really do this. It’s going to be detrimental to his health, but he wants to do it, so it’s signed and it’s happening!”

AFC Totton.'.
caption:
Dorking Wanderers say they intend to hand 54-year-old fan Terry Dunn a debut in goal in their National League South fixture against AFC Totton on Saturday 🤯🧤

‘Big Tel’, who has previously played for several local clubs, retired in 1997 but has signed a short-term contract with the club, due to Wanderers’ first-team goalkeeper Harrison Foulkes being ruled out for up to four weeks with a spleen injury 🤕❌

🗣️ Dunn: “Playing in goal is like riding a bike – you never forget it. I still regularly play walking football. As a Wanderers fan, no-one will be trying harder than me to keep a clean sheet on Saturday.”

🗣️ Manager Marc White: “In an era where passion comes in low quantities, what Terry lacks in mobility, he’ll make up for in heart – and for one game, we’re just going to have to get on with it.”

Best of luck on Saturday, ‘Big Tel’ 👏

📸 @dwfcofficial

alt: Photo by SPORTbible on August 21, 2025. May be an image of 5 people, people playing tennis, people standing, racket and text.
caption:
Ben Chilwell has donated £25,000 towards a charity set up to help find a cure for childhood brain tumours, after sadly losing one of his biggest fans, aged just 13 💔

Shay Patel was a Chelsea fan whose favourite player was Chilwell, with the two having an extra connection of having played for grassroots club Woburn Lions, near Milton Keynes ⚽️🔵

The 13-year-old sadly passed away from a glioblastoma brain tumour, and the England left-back is now a patron of the Shay Smiles charity, and he accompanied Shay’s parents to the Brain Tumour Research Centre of Excellence this week at Queen Mary’s Hospital in London 🏥

🗣️ “Until I met Shay’s parents, Niki and Deenu, I wasn’t aware how tough the outlook was for brain tumour patients. It was shocking to discover that one in three children who die of cancer is killed by a brain tumour.”

A beautiful gesture from Chilwell 👏❤️

📸 @brain_tumour_research

caption:
British three-time Speedway World Champion Tai Woffinden was back on a speedway bike, just 4 months after fearing for his life and being in an induced coma after suffering life-threatening injuries in a crash in Poland 🚴🤯

Woffinden was airlifted to hospital after the incident, where he picked up the following injuries:

Double compound right femur fracture
Broken back
Right humerus compound fracture
Dislocated + smashed right elbow
12 broken ribs + punctured lung
Left broken shoulderblade
Dislocated left shoulder
Lost 3 litres of blood and needed blood transfusion

He was discharged from hospital just 19 days after the crash, and since then he has rehabbed for 4-5 hours a day for 5 days of the week 💪🏋️

Incredible mentality and mindset from the 31-year-old 💪👏

May be an image of 4 people, people golfing, magazine, golf course and text that says 'TT SPORT BIBLE IT FEELS LIKE YOU WORK YOUR WHOLE LIFE TO CELEBRATE WINNING A A GOLF TOURNAMENT FOR LIKE A FEW MINUTES WOULD MUCH RATHER BE BETTER FATHER THAN WOULD BE A GREAT GOLFER! THAT'S WHAT'S MORE IMPORTANT TO ME'.
caption:
Golfer Scottie Scheffler gave an incredibly deep answer when asked what it means to win and be the World No.1, sharing he’d rather be remembered as a great father than a great golfer 🏌️🥹

🗣️ “Is it great to be able to win tournaments and to accomplish the things I have in the game of golf? Yeah I mean it brings a tears to my eyes just thinking about it because it’s what I literally worked my whole life to become good at the sport and that sense of accomplishment, I think it’s a pretty cool feeling... but at the end of the day I’m not here to inspire the next generation of golfers. I don’t.

“I’m not here to inspire somebody else to be the best player in the world, because what’s the point? You know, this is not a fulfilling life. It’s fulfilling from the sense of the accomplishment, but it’s not fulfilling from a sense of like, the deepest places of your heart... You’re like, why do I want to win this tournament so bad? That’s something that I wrestle with on a daily basis.

“It’s like showing up at the Masters every year. Why do I want to win this golf tournament so badly? Why do I want to win The Open Championship so badly? I don’t know, because if I win, it’s going to be awesome for two minutes.”

Nothing but honesty from Scheffler 👏

alt: Photo by SPORTbible on March 18, 2025.
caption:
Bulgarian football club Arda Kardzhali apologised after holding a minute's silence for their former player, Petko Ganchev, who is still alive 🤯

78-year-old Ganchev said he arrived back home early in the first-half to find his wife in tears after watching the minute's silence on TV 😳

🗣️ "I was about ten minutes late for the game against Levski because I had some work to do. As I was driving home, my phone started ringing a lot but I was driving and I didn’t dare to answer.

"I entered the garden and my wife greeted me in tears. She said, ‘Petko, Petko, they’ve announced on TV that you’ve passed away!’ I couldn’t understand what she was saying or what had happened."

At half-time, the football club sent an email to the TV station broadcasting the match to confirm that they had made a mistake and that Ganchev was still alive 😬

🗣️ "The management of PFC Arda would like to express a huge apology to the former Arda player Petko Ganchev and his relatives after the club received wrong information about his death. We wish Petko Ganchev many more years of good health and to enjoy the success of Arda."

A very embarrassing moment for the Bulgarian club 🫣
